 Timothy R. Jackson, Margaret Littler, Rachel MagShamráin, Frauke Matthes, Yomb May, Jeffrey Morrison, Kate Roy, Monika Shafi, Edwin Wieringa, W. Daniel Wilson,Karin E. Yesilada. James Hodkinson is Assistant Professor of German at Warwick University; Jeffrey Morrison is Senior Lecturer at the National University of Ireland, Maynooth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEast and West in literature. 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aIslam in literature. 0aIslamxRelationsxChristianity. 0aOrientalism in literature. 0aOther (Philosophy) in literature. 4aEarly Modern History. 4aEnglish & American Literature. 4aGerman Literature. 4aWomen's & Gender Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aCultural Encounters.  aGerman Literature.  aGerman-Turkish Community.  aHybrid Origins.  aIslam.1 aEdwards, Cyril, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFalkner, Silke R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHodkinson, James R, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHodkinson, James R, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHodkinson, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Timothy R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Timothy Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLittler, Margaret, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagShamhráin, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatthes, Frauke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMay, Yomb, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorrison, Jeff, econtributor.4ctb4https://id